```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    if !isdate(dt) && isinteger(bump)
        return DateTime(floor(time(dt)) + 60*60*bump)
    else
        throw(ArgumentError("Input must be a DateTime and bump must be an integer"))
    end
end
```

This function `timezone_bumper` takes two arguments: `dt`, which should be a `DateTime`, and `bump`, which defaults to 3 hours if not provided. The function returns a new `DateTime` with the time component increased by `bump` hours. If `dt` is not a `DateTime` or `bump` is not an integer, an `ArgumentError` is thrown.
